        content: "Start with the numbers from your tracking month. Say: Last month I spent 92 hours on Mom's care and $640 out of pocket. Here is the breakdown. I want us to talk about how to handle this going forward as a family. Hand or screen-share the spreadsheet. The data shifts the conversation from a sibling accusing you of complaining to a family looking together at a real situation. Most siblings respond better to data than to emotional pleas. Save the feelings for later in the conversation, after the facts have landed.",
